      "content": "##|Petals|and|Putrefaction|Zoey|Yamashita|walked|through|the|busy|Tokyo|street|.|People|rushed|past|her|,|a|river|of|sound|and|color|.|For|her|,|it|was|mostly|noise|.|Four|hundred|years|of|noise|.|Her|eyes|,|however|,|caught|something|small|,|white|,|and|still|.|It|was|a|single|chrysanthemum|flower|,|wilted|and|brown|at|the|edges|.|Someone|had|probably|dropped|it|,|or|maybe|it|fell|from|a|small|offering|at|a|shop|.|Zoey|stopped|.|This|was|not|normal|for|her|.|She|did|not|usually|notice|such|things|.|But|the|flower|,|pale|and|dying|,|looked…|peaceful|.|She|bent|down|.|Her|fingers|,|long|and|careful|,|picked|it|up|.|It|felt|soft|,|like|old|paper|.|The|petals|were|thin|and|tired|.|A|white|chrysanthemum|.|A|*kiku*|.|Often|seen|at|funerals|in|Japan|.|How|fitting|.|But|then|,|a|strange|thing|happened|.|A|tiny|flicker|,|like|a|faraway|light|,|touched|her|mind|.|It|was|not|a|picture|.|It|was|a|feeling|.|A|feeling|of|*warmth*|.|Of|soft|ground|under|bare|feet|.|The|quiet|sound|of…|water|?|And|then|,|a|perfect|white|flower|,|impossibly|bright|,|shining|in|the|sun|.|A|quick|,|clear|sense|of|being|very|,|very|*small*|.|Zoey|frowned|.|\"|How|annoying|,|\"|she|whispered|to|the|wilting|flower|in|her|hand|.|This|was|a|*memory*|.|A|human|memory|.|Something|she|rarely|felt|,|and|never|truly|understood|anymore|.|It|was|a|fragment|from|a|life|she|no|longer|lived|,|a|time|when|she|was|just|a|girl|,|before|the|change|.|And|it|was|almost…|pleasant|.|That|was|the|truly|unsettling|part|.|\"|A|ghost|of|a|feeling|,|\"|she|thought|,|looking|at|the|dead|flower|.|\"|And|it|'|s|telling|me|to|do|something|stupid|.|\"|But|the|feeling|,|faint|as|it|was|,|held|her|.|She|wanted|to|see|a|*living*|one|.|A|perfect|,|bright|white|chrysanthemum|.|Not|just|any|chrysanthemum|.|One|that|felt|like|*that*|.|An|impossible|task|,|she|knew|.|Her|life|was|about|hiding|,|not|about|chasing|fleeting|human|emotions|.|Yet|,|she|found|herself|walking|,|the|wilting|flower|still|clutched|in|her|hand|.|First|,|she|went|to|a|flower|shop|.|The|shop|was|small|and|filled|with|many|bright|flowers|.|The|air|smelled|sweet|.|A|young|woman|with|a|kind|smile|greeted|Zoey|.|\"|Can|I|help|you|?|\"|the|woman|asked|.|\"|A|white|chrysanthemum|,|\"|Zoey|said|.|Her|voice|was|flat|.|\"|A|very|good|one|.|Perfect|.|\"|The|woman|showed|her|a|large|bunch|of|white|chrysanthemums|.|They|were|fresh|,|green|stems|,|white|petals|.|But|Zoey|shook|her|head|.|\"|No|.|Not|like|these|.|\"|The|woman|looked|confused|.|\"|They|are|very|fresh|.|Just|arrived|this|morning|.|\"|\"|Too|bright|,|\"|Zoey|thought|.|\"|Too|fake|.|Not|the|ghost|.|\"|She|turned|and|left|the|shop|.|The|flowers|there|were|too|full|of|life|,|a|life|she|couldn|'|t|share|.|She|walked|through|a|large|park|.|People|sat|on|benches|,|laughed|with|friends|,|played|with|children|.|Zoey|watched|them|,|feeling|the|familiar|distance|.|So|much|energy|.|For|what|?|To|live|and|then|to|die|?|Her|own|non-life|was|much|simpler|,|if|more|boring|.|She|saw|small|gardens|in|the|park|,|but|no|white|chrysanthemums|that|looked|like|her|fading|memory|.|The|wilting|flower|in|her|hand|seemed|to|shrink|a|little|more|with|each|step|.|Just|then|,|she|saw|him|.|Detective|Kuroda|.|He|was|talking|to|a|park|guard|.|His|eyes|,|always|looking|,|always|suspicious|,|found|hers|.|He|paused|,|just|for|a|second|,|and|gave|her|a|small|,|sharp|look|.|Zoey|met|his|gaze|with|her|usual|blank|stare|,|then|walked|on|.|\"|Humans|,|\"|she|thought|.|\"|Always|looking|for|something|that|isn|'|t|there|.|\"|Or|,|in|her|case|,|something|that|*is*|there|but|shouldn|'|t|be|.|The|hunt|was|useless|.|Zoey|felt|a|surge|of|her|usual|boredom|.|This|flower|chase|was|a|waste|of|a|perfectly|good|afternoon|.|\"|Maybe|some|things|are|better|left|dead|,|\"|she|thought|.|\"|Like|me|.|Less|trouble|.|\"|Then|,|a|new|thought|came|to|her|.|A|morbid|one|.|If|she|wanted|an|\"|eternal|\"|flower|,|where|would|she|find|it|?|Not|in|a|shop|full|of|living|things|.|She|pulled|out|her|phone|and|sent|a|quick|message|to|Lex|,|her|fellow|immortal|zombie|.|Lex|loved|being|undead|.|He|found|joy|in|things|Zoey|found|only|boredom|in|.|\"|Lex|,|\"|she|typed|.|\"|Where|would|one|find|a|truly|*eternal*|white|flower|?|Asking|for|a|friend|.|My|friend|is|me|.|And|I|'|m|looking|for|a|flower|.|\"|Lex|'|s|reply|came|almost|at|once|.|\"|Eternal|?|You|mean|plastic|,|Zoey|?|Or|maybe|at|a|very|well-kept|grave|?|What|'|s|going|on|?|Feeling|sentimental|?|\"|\"|Sentimental|?|Don|'|t|be|ridiculous|.|It|'|s|a|scientific|inquiry|,|\"|Zoey|typed|back|.|But|Lex|'|s|idea|of|a|\"|well-kept|grave|\"|gave|her|a|new|path|.|She|found|herself|walking|towards|an|old|,|quiet|part|of|the|city|.|There|was|a|very|old|cemetery|there|,|with|tall|trees|and|stone|lanterns|.|It|was|peaceful|,|mostly|empty|.|Many|graves|had|small|flower|offerings|.|Many|of|them|were|white|chrysanthemums|.|Some|were|plastic|,|looking|fake|and|too|bright|.|Others|were|real|,|but|already|wilting|,|just|like|the|one|in|her|hand|.|The|irony|was|heavy|.|Even|here|,|among|the|dead|,|life|was|a|short|,|fading|thing|.|As|the|sun|began|to|set|,|painting|the|sky|in|soft|oranges|and|purples|,|Zoey|felt|a|pull|towards|a|small|bookstore|.|Takashi|'|s|bookstore|.|It|was|a|comfort|,|a|small|island|of|calm|.|She|entered|,|the|small|bell|above|the|door|ringing|softly|.|Takashi|looked|up|from|a|book|,|his|smile|gentle|.|\"|Zoey-san|.|Good|evening|.|\"|\"|Good|evening|,|Takashi-san|,|\"|Zoey|replied|.|She|held|up|the|wilting|flower|.|\"|Do|you|know|anything|about|these|flowers|?|White|chrysanthemums|?|\"|Takashi|looked|at|the|flower|,|then|at|Zoey|'|s|blank|face|.|\"|Ah|,|the|kiku|.|They|are|beautiful|.|In|Japan|,|they|often|mean|purity|,|truth|,|and|loyalty|.|They|are|very|popular|for|important|events|,|like|festivals|,|and|also…|for|remembering|those|who|have|passed|.|\"|He|paused|,|looking|at|her|carefully|.|\"|They|are|very|hardy|flowers|.|Some|old|temple|gardens|have|special|varieties|,|cared|for|over|many|generations|.|There|'|s|a|small|temple|,|not|far|from|here|,|just|past|the|old|bridge|.|It|has|a|very|old|garden|,|well-hidden|.|They|say|special|flowers|grow|there|.|\"|Zoey|felt|a|flicker|of|something|in|her|chest|.|Not|joy|,|not|hope|.|Just|a|strange|urge|to|see|it|.|\"|Thank|you|,|\"|she|said|,|her|voice|softer|than|usual|.|She|left|the|bookstore|.|She|walked|towards|the|old|bridge|Takashi|mentioned|.|The|streets|grew|quieter|,|the|houses|older|.|She|found|a|small|,|narrow|path|she|had|never|noticed|before|.|It|led|to|a|small|,|wooden|gate|.|Beyond|it|,|a|tiny|,|ancient|temple|stood|.|And|beside|it|,|a|garden|.|It|was|not|a|grand|garden|.|It|was|small|,|green|,|and|perfectly|kept|.|And|there|,|in|a|corner|,|was|a|patch|of|white|chrysanthemums|.|They|were|perfect|.|Their|petals|were|bright|white|,|unblemished|,|strong|.|They|stood|tall|,|almost|glowing|in|the|fading|light|.|They|looked|impossible|.|They|looked|like|they|could|last|forever|.|Zoey|stood|there|,|looking|.|She|didn|'|t|pick|one|.|She|didn|'|t|touch|them|.|They|were|exactly|like|the|image|,|the|feeling|,|from|her|memory|.|They|were|living|,|breathing|proof|that|the|ghost|of|a|feeling|was|real|.|And|for|a|brief|moment|,|the|faint|memory|came|back|,|clearer|this|time|.|The|soft|dirt|,|the|green|smell|after|rain|,|a|gentle|breeze|,|and|the|feeling|of|warmth|on|her|small|face|.|A|simple|,|quiet|happiness|.|A|moment|from|a|life|so|far|away|it|was|almost|a|dream|.|A|life|when|she|was|just|*human*|.|Then|,|like|smoke|,|it|faded|.|The|perfect|chrysanthemums|were|just|flowers|.|The|memory|was|just|a|memory|,|unreachable|.|She|looked|at|the|wilting|flower|still|in|her|hand|.|It|was|almost|completely|brown|now|.|Its|petals|drooped|,|almost|touching|her|palm|.|It|looked|tired|,|dead|.|Like|a|part|of|her|.|Zoey|turned|and|walked|away|from|the|temple|garden|.|The|streetlights|flickered|on|as|night|came|.|\"|A|useless|day|,|\"|she|thought|.|\"|Chasing|a|ghost|of|a|ghost|.|How|pathetic|.|\"|She|walked|past|a|public|trash|can|.|Without|thinking|,|without|a|single|soft|feeling|,|she|let|the|wilting|white|chrysanthemum|fall|from|her|hand|.|The|wind|caught|it|for|a|second|,|then|it|dropped|,|forgotten|,|into|the|bin|.|Even|a|400-year-old|zombie|,|it|seemed|,|could|be|fooled|by|a|pretty|flower|.|But|only|for|a|moment|.|Her|existence|was|eternal|.|But|beautiful|things|,|like|flowers|and|human|memories|,|were|not|.|And|that|,|she|knew|,|was|a|kind|of|sad|truth|.",
